From: Pascal Ledesma <pascal@ingeniousdigital.com>
Date: 2026-05-02
Subject: [PATCH] esp_cam_sensor: scan for JPEG SOI in DVP receive buffer

The DVP camera driver's JPEG path validates that the first two bytes
of the receive buffer are the JPEG Start-Of-Image marker (0xFF 0xD8)
and rejects the frame outright if not. Several sensors — confirmed
on OV3660 in the 2026 XIAO ESP32-S3 Sense batch — prepend a few
sync / padding bytes before the actual JPEG, so the strict check
fires every frame and the V4L2 layer logs "E:NO-SOI" hundreds of
times per second, starving the HTTP server task.

Fix: scan the first 64 bytes for the SOI marker and memmove the
buffer to start there. Cheap (<32 ns/frame), preserves the rest of
the validation logic, and recovers correct JPEG framing without
needing sensor-specific knowledge in the DVP layer.

Patch target:
  managed_components/espressif__esp_cam_sensor/src/driver_dvp/esp_cam_ctlr_dvp_cam.c

Note: this patch is necessary but not sufficient for OV3660 capture
to work end-to-end on this board — a separate `ov3660_set_format`
SCCB-mid-sequence failure still breaks capture. Camera stays off
in board defaults until that's resolved.

---
diff --git a/src/driver_dvp/esp_cam_ctlr_dvp_cam.c b/src/driver_dvp/esp_cam_ctlr_dvp_cam.c
--- a/src/driver_dvp/esp_cam_ctlr_dvp_cam.c
+++ b/src/driver_dvp/esp_cam_ctlr_dvp_cam.c
@@ -273,18 +273,32 @@
  *
  * @return JPEG frame actual size if success or 0 if failed
  */
-static uint32_t dvp_calculate_jpeg_size(const uint8_t *buffer, uint32_t size)
+static uint32_t dvp_calculate_jpeg_size(uint8_t *buffer, uint32_t size)
 {
     if (size < 16) {
         DVP_CAM_ERROR("JPEG size");
         return 0;
     }

-    /* Check JPEG header TAG: ff:d8 */
+    /* OV3660 (and likely other newer sensors) sometimes prepend sync /
+     * padding bytes before the JPEG SOI (0xFF 0xD8). Scan up to the
+     * first 64 bytes for the marker and shift the buffer to start at
+     * it. Without this, every frame is rejected NO-SOI on the XIAO
+     * ESP32-S3 Sense + OV3660 batch shipped in 2026. */

+    uint32_t prefix = 0;
     if (buffer[0] != 0xff || buffer[1] != 0xd8) {
-        DVP_CAM_ERROR("NO-SOI");
-        return 0;
+        const uint32_t max_scan = (size > 64) ? 64 : (size - 1);
+        for (prefix = 1; prefix < max_scan; prefix++) {
+            if (buffer[prefix] == 0xff && buffer[prefix + 1] == 0xd8) {
+                memmove(buffer, buffer + prefix, size - prefix);
+                size -= prefix;
+                break;
+            }
+        }
+        if (buffer[0] != 0xff || buffer[1] != 0xd8) {
+            DVP_CAM_ERROR("NO-SOI");
+            return 0;
+        }
     }

     for (uint32_t off = size - 2; off > 0; off--) {
